        "details": {
            "description": "<p>The <em>Eternity Arch</em> sparks with electricity, releasing bolts of lightning at each of the four largest time rifts.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[type:thievery|dc:23] (trained) or @Check[type:arcana|dc:21]&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">(trained)</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">, @Check[type:nature|dc:21]&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">(trained)</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">, @Check[type:occultism|dc:21]&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">(trained)</span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">, or @Check[type:religion|dc:21] (trained) to seal each of the four time rifts, @Check[type:crafting|dc:23] (trained) to divert the lightning to another source, or </span><em style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Dispel Magic]{Dispel Magic}</em><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"> (2nd level; counteract DC 20) to counteract each time rift. Each attempt requires 2 actions. Skill checks to disable a time rift must attempted from adjacent to the rift.</span></p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 5
            },
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p>(4 actions) The trap loses 1 action each turn for each disabled time rift. On each of the trap's actions, the <em>Eternity Arch</em> releases a bolt of lightning that activates that rift, dealing [[/r {2d8}[electricity]]]{2d8 electricity damage} to all creatures in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:10] around the time rift (@Check[type:reflex|dc:22|basic:true] save). It can release a bolt at each active time rift no more than once each turn.</p>"
        },
